{"title_page": "List of people from Hayward, California", "text_new": "This is a '''list of people from Hayward, California'''. People from [[Hayward, California|Hayward]] who are strongly associated with the city include founder [[William Dutton Hayward]], and the [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] patriot and [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Greek Orthodox]] priest [[Agapius Honcharenko]], who created a farm whose location is now a historic landmark. High-profile people from Hayward include football coach [[Bill Walsh (American football coach)|Bill Walsh]], figure skater [[Kristi Yamaguchi]], wrestler and film star [[Dwayne Johnson]], and [[Treasurer of the United States]] [[Rosa Gumataotao Rios]]. [[Charles Plummer (sheriff)|Charles Plummer]], prior to becoming [[Alameda County Sheriff's Office|Alameda County Sheriff]], was the Police Chief of Hayward.\n\n[[File:Walsh and tomey.jpg|thumb|[[Bill Walsh (American football coach)|Bill Walsh]] (left) with [[Dick Tomey]]]]\n\nPeople born ('''b'''), raised ('''r''') (including attending high school in Hayward), or who have lived as adults ('''a''') in Hayward ('''bold names''' are current residents):\n<!-- Please alphabetize by surname, with each listing ordered by name, with YOB/YOD, residency status ('''b''' for born, '''r'''for raised, '''a''' if lived there as an adult), and brief description of their notability. Names without an existing article, or without references showing notability and past/present residency in the city itself (not business ownership or college attendance) will be removed. -->\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:BrianCopeland.jpg|thumb|150px|right|[[Brian Copeland]]]] -->\n* [[Sena Acolatse]] (1990\u2013) ('''b'''), hockey player\n* [[Mahershala Ali]] (1974\u2013) ('''b''','''r'''), Academy Award-winning actor\n* [[Glen Alvelais]] (1968\u2013) ('''b'''), [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]] guitarist for [[Forbidden (band)|Forbidden]]<ref>{{cite web \n* [[Johnny Ray Montanio]] (1970-)\n('''b'''), [[Hardcore punk|punkrock|thrash]] song writer|bassist for [[No Remorse|implant|forty43three (bands)\n\n|url=http://www.glenalvelais.com/about-me |title=About Me |publisher=Glenalvelais.com |date=February 22, 1968 |accessdate=November 13, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120207102807/http://www.glenalvelais.com/about-me |archivedate=February 7, 2012 }}</ref>\n* [[Max Baer (boxer)|Max Baer]] (1909\u20131959) ('''a'''), boxer from the 1930s,  [[List of Heavyweight Champions|Heavyweight Champion of the World]], actor<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.maxbaer.org/earlyyears.html |title=Welcome to MaxBaer.org \u2013 Family !! |publisher=Maxbaer.org |accessdate=November 13, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111123013509/http://www.maxbaer.org/earlyyears.html |archivedate=November 23, 2011 }}</ref>\n* [[Chauncey Bailey]] (October 20, 1949 \u2013 August 2, 2007) ('''r'''), murdered Oakland journalist\n* [[Jeff Barnes]] (1955\u2013) ('''r'''), National Football League linebacker<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.databasefootball.com/players/playerpage.htm?ilkid=BARNEJEF01 |title=RotoWire Fantasy Football, Baseball, Basketball and More |accessdate=2012-12-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130421102737/http://www.databasefootball.com/players/playerpage.htm?ilkid=BARNEJEF01 |archivedate=2013-04-21 }}</ref>\n* [[Brian Beacock]] (1966\u2013) ('''b'''), [[anime]] voice performer and actor<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/people/brian-beacock/ |title=Brian Beacock |publisher=TV.com |date=March 14, 2007 |accessdate=November 13, 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Jeff Beal]] (1963\u2013) ('''b'''), jazz instrumentalist, [[Emmy award]]-winning film and television music composer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jeffbeal.com/Pages/PressPages/JeffBealBio.html |title=Jeff Beal.com JEFF's STORY |publisher=Jeffbeal.com |accessdate=November 13, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111125053104/http://www.jeffbeal.com/Pa